setHttpInterfaceAddress

public void setHttpInterfaceAddress(String address)
Sets the HTTP interface Address to bind the outgoing HTTP transport (

e.g. "192.168.1.1").

Remember that HTTP is not a symmetric transport (like TCP). This interface address is for request going out from this peer.

Parameters:
address - the address value

setHttpPublicAddress

public void setHttpPublicAddress(String address,
                                 boolean exclusive)
Sets the HTTP JXTA Public Address for incoming http requests (e.g. "133.42.7.28:9700").

Remember that HTTP is not a symmetric transport (like TCP). This interface address is for request coming to this peer.

The exclusive boolean indicate whether this address should be use for both incoming and outgoing http requests. This is sometimes necessary when peers are located behind NAT and firewalls.

Parameters:
address - the HTTP transport public address
exclusive - determines whether this address should advertised exclusively

getHttpPublicAddress

HTTP public address configuration

public boolean getHttpPublicAddressExclusive()

Returns:
HTTP public address exclusive use
